{"questionId":"9067254","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Phosphatidylcholine is an example of a phospholipid found in lecithin.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Phosphatidylcholine may be formed from propane-1,2,3-triol, two lauric acid molecules, phosphoric acid and the choline cation.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3ceda054831af77090fe92b52e6cdd8bb12f3f85.png\" width=\"698\" height=\"97\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Deduce the structural formula of phosphatidylcholine.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f25a2af05ad57711b03d8b07d530eed1d5611c34.png\" width=\"77\" height=\"162\"></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/33ea2b9f02002c7490450c9eca84d3b80f96df3f.png\" width=\"398\" height=\"259\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">phosphodiester correctly drawn&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">both ester groups correctly drawn <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong> Note:</strong>&nbsp;Accept protonated phosphate. </span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Accept phosphodiester in centre position.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067254","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.a(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the structural formula of phosphatidylcholine.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.3 Lipids","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}